{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "web:job.35",
    "translationId": "web",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 35,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 35",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 35 in World English Bible."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "web:job.35.1",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 35:1",
      "text": "Moreover Elihu answered,",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.35.2",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 35:2",
      "text": "“Do you think this to be your right, or do you say, ‘ My righteousness is more than God’s,’",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.35.3",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 35:3",
      "text": "that you ask, ‘ What advantage will it be to you? What profit will I have, more than if I had sinned?’",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.35.4",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 35:4",
      "text": "I will answer you, and your companions with you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.35.5",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 35:5",
      "text": "Look to the skies, and see. See the skies, which are higher than you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.35.6",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 35:6",
      "text": "If you have sinned, what effect do you have against him? If your transgressions are multiplied, what do you do to him?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.35.7",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 35:7",
      "text": "If you are righteous, what do you give him? Or what does he receive from your hand?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.35.8",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 35:8",
      "text": "Your wickedness may hurt a man as you are, and your righteousness may profit a son of man.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.35.9",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 35:9",
      "text": "“ By reason of the multitude of oppressions they cry out. They cry for help by reason of the arm of the mighty.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.35.10",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 35:10",
      "text": "But no one says, ‘ Where is God my Maker, who gives songs in the night,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.35.11",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 35:11",
      "text": "who teaches us more than the animals of the earth, and makes us wiser than the birds of the sky?’",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.35.12",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 35:12",
      "text": "There they cry, but no one answers, because of the pride of evil men.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.35.13",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 35:13",
      "text": "Surely God will not hear an empty cry, neither will the Almighty regard it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.35.14",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 35:14",
      "text": "How much less when you say you don’t see him. The cause is before him, and you wait for him!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.35.15",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 35:15",
      "text": "But now, because he has not visited in his anger, neither does he greatly regard arrogance,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.35.16",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 35,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 35:16",
      "text": "therefore Job opens his mouth with empty talk, and he multiplies words without knowledge.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
